Charles F. Miller https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_F._Miller 0 Charles F. Miller (June 6, 1878 – November 25, 1952) was an American film actor. Miller made his film debut in Little Women as a minister and starred in many films thereafter. One of his first biggest roles was starring alongside Keye Luke in Phantom of Chinatown. He was also one of the founding members of the Screen Actors Guild. Charles_F._Miller ( June_6_,_1878 – November_25_,_1952 ) was an_American_film_actor .
